The paper deals with a problem of secure communication in the context of group testing, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of adaptive algorithms and private feedback links suggests a focus on data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG), while the need to ensure negligible mutual information at the eavesdropper points to a potential interest in security and privacy (cs.SI).
